Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 aims-os-desktop,
# --- Web & Android Development ---------------------------------------
# default-jdk    Java 21 (Trixie default). Required by Android Studio,
#                Gradle, Spring Boot, Tomcat.
# gradle         Android's official build tool. The Android Studio
#                bundle uses its own gradle-wrapper but a system gradle
#                lets command-line builds work offline.
# kotlin         Android's first-class language since 2019.
# php-cli +      LAMP-side of the Web course (Laravel, Symfony,
# composer       vanilla PHP).
# android-tools- flash and debug Android devices over USB for the
#   adb/fastboot Android Development course hardware labs.
 default-jdk,
 gradle,
 kotlin,
 php-cli,
 composer,
 android-tools-adb,
 android-tools-fastboot,
# --- Containers & orchestration --------------------------------------
# docker.io      Docker Engine (Moby) — 26.1.5 in Trixie. Pulls
#                containerd as a dep.
# docker-compose Compose V2 (Go binary 2.26.1 in Trixie, kept under the
#                legacy package name). Invoked as `docker compose ...`.
# docker-buildx  Multi-arch / multi-stage container builds.
# podman         Daemonless, rootless container runtime alternative.
# kubectl        Kubernetes CLI (v1.32 in Trixie). MLOps / cloud labs.
# ansible        Automation / deployment workflows.
 docker.io,
 docker-compose,
 docker-buildx,
 podman,
 kubectl,
 ansible,
# --- Rust toolchain manager ------------------------------------------
# Trixie ships rustc 1.85 directly; rustup is for users who want
# stable/nightly toolchain switching on demand.
 rustup,
Description: AIMS OS — heavy development stack (Java, Android, containers, Rust)
 The full development layer carved out of the v2.0 aims-os-desktop.
 Installs the Java / Android / Web / containers / Rust toolchains.
 About 2 GB on disk after install — kept out of the live ISO so it
 only lands on machines that actually need it.
 .
 Covers:
   * Web & Android Development course — OpenJDK 21, Gradle, Kotlin,
     PHP / Composer, adb / fastboot.
   * Containers & orchestration (Web/Android + MLOps + Big Data labs)
     — Docker Engine + Compose v2 + Buildx, Podman, kubectl, Ansible.
   * Rust toolchain manager (rustup) for users who want stable/nightly
     switching on top of Trixie's rustc 1.85.
 .
 Android Studio itself stays install-on-demand via Flatpak
 (com.google.AndroidStudio on Flathub) — apt-shipping it would pin
 it to whatever version Debian Trixie froze at release.
